tweet: The OEV Relay manages the auction process, using reputation scores and unconditional bids to prevent searcher misbehaviour.    This service will not be reliant on private mempools or any outside services, empowering OEV internalisation across all blockchains with data feeds.
name: API3

tweet: API3 will provide app-specific OEV data feeds to allow for auction proceeds to be accurately distributed to the dApp generating the value.
name: API3

tweet: Third parties improving data feed granularity will minimise value loss from arbitrage and frontrunning, while protecting lender capital with timely liquidations.    The off-chain auction maximises capital returned to liquidated borrowers, and reduces spam on the network.
name: API3

tweet: The main difference between this solution and generalised OF auctions is that third parties can request OF on demand.   This operates alongside the existing oracle updates being performed, maintaining security guarantees for the data feed.
name: API3

tweet: OEV auctions are an innovative new type of permissionless OF auction designed to maximise value capture for LPs of DeFi apps using data feeds.   By driving revenue for LPs, better services can be provided that improve user-experience and grow the DeFi ecosystem.
name: API3

tweet: API3’s OEV data feeds allow for dApps to begin capturing much of this value to distribute back to their stakeholders and users.   It starts with reimagining Order Flow (OF) auctions.
name: API3

tweet: Traditional oracle designs have limited DeFi apps by causing them to suffer significant value loss through a subset of MEV termed Oracle Extractable Value (OEV). The majority of OEV extracted from dApps is captured by block producers and searchers  Until now…
name: API3
